getAdjustedEnterpriseList

public static java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> getAdjustedEnterpriseList(oracle.jbo.server.DBTransaction dbt,
                                                                                         boolean isFND)
                                                                                  throws java.sql.SQLException
sjanarth, Nov 2011 For OVM environments, a single LDAP store is shared across multiple instances. Therefore, the enterprise ids used are expected to be unique across all the instances. With this mind, OVMs create a unique enterprise id and move all the seed data from eid=1 to eid=newid. For ATG, an admts based wrapper script makes a copy of the seed data from eid=1 to eid=newid. HCM tables, on the other hand, primarily because the PKs in them are not striped with enterprise id, cannot take advantage of admts. Since admts is not used for such tables, there is no need for a 'template' enterprise. Therefore, for HCM tables, the data is simply moved from eid=1 to eid=newid. When SDF comes along (as a part of general patching or RUPs), the HCM API that exposes the list of enterprises, returns two enterprises (1, newid). This, while works fine for ATG tables, poses a problem for HCM as HCM seed data is no longer present in eid=1. The fundamental gap here is that, unlike ATG, HCM seed data is moved instead of being copied. Since RUP1 is blocked, figuring out a way to make a copy of HCM seed data is not an option. Just to get RUP1 out, SDF will 'fudge' the enterprise list fo drop eid=1 when loading HCM seed data. This is being viwed as an interim solution for RUP1.

Parameters:
dbt -
isFND -
Returns:
the adjusted list of entries
Throws:
java.sql.SQLException
